<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="89">
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="89">Collum</emphasis>
: crests complete and evident; carinotaxy formula I-III+P+M (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 14" captionStartId="F14" captionText="Figure 14. Glyphiulus portaliformis Zhao &amp; Liu, sp. nov., ♂ paratype A, B anterior body rings, dorsal and lateral views C, D mid-body rings, dorsal and lateral views, respectively E, F posterior body rings, dorsal and ventral views, respectively. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1108.85156.figure14" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/705264" pageId="0" pageNumber="89">14A, B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 15" captionStartId="F15" captionText="Figure 15. Glyphiulus portaliformis Zhao &amp; Liu, sp. nov., ♂ paratype A gnathochilarium and left antenna B head and collum C penes D mid-leg and claw E leg 3, caudal view F leg 1, frontal view G ♀ paratype, vulvae H anterior gonopods, caudal view I, J posterior gonopod, caudal and frontal views, respectively. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A, B, D, E), 0.2 mm (C, F-J)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1108.85156.figure15" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/705265" pageId="0" pageNumber="89">15B</figureCitation>
). Following metaterga strongly crested; carinotaxy formula 2/2+I/i+3/3 (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 14" captionStartId="F14" captionText="Figure 14. Glyphiulus portaliformis Zhao &amp; Liu, sp. nov., ♂ paratype A, B anterior body rings, dorsal and lateral views C, D mid-body rings, dorsal and lateral views, respectively E, F posterior body rings, dorsal and ventral views, respectively. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1108.85156.figure14" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/705264" pageId="0" pageNumber="89">14</figureCitation>
). Ozoporiferous tubercles very large, coniform. Prozonae delicately alveolate-areolate, fine longitudinal striations in front of stricture. Metazonae with an obvious, corrugate, carved texture (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 14" captionStartId="F14" captionText="Figure 14. Glyphiulus portaliformis Zhao &amp; Liu, sp. nov., ♂ paratype A, B anterior body rings, dorsal and lateral views C, D mid-body rings, dorsal and lateral views, respectively E, F posterior body rings, dorsal and ventral views, respectively. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1108.85156.figure14" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/705264" pageId="0" pageNumber="89">14</figureCitation>
). Rings 2 and 3 with long pleural flaps.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="89">
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="89">Epiproct</emphasis>
simple, caudal edge with a central conical protrusion and dorsally with a strong central rounded tubercle (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 14" captionStartId="F14" captionText="Figure 14. Glyphiulus portaliformis Zhao &amp; Liu, sp. nov., ♂ paratype A, B anterior body rings, dorsal and lateral views C, D mid-body rings, dorsal and lateral views, respectively E, F posterior body rings, dorsal and ventral views, respectively. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1108.85156.figure14" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/705264" pageId="0" pageNumber="89">14E</figureCitation>
). Paraprocts regularly convex, each with several irregular rows of setae. Hypoproct transversely bean-shaped, no setae visible (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 14" captionStartId="F14" captionText="Figure 14. Glyphiulus portaliformis Zhao &amp; Liu, sp. nov., ♂ paratype A, B anterior body rings, dorsal and lateral views C, D mid-body rings, dorsal and lateral views, respectively E, F posterior body rings, dorsal and ventral views, respectively. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1108.85156.figure14" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/705264" pageId="0" pageNumber="89">14F</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="89">
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="89">Legs</emphasis>
slender, about 1.1 times as long as mid-body height; claw with a small accessory spine at base, about 1/5 as long as claw (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 15" captionStartId="F15" captionText="Figure 15. Glyphiulus portaliformis Zhao &amp; Liu, sp. nov., ♂ paratype A gnathochilarium and left antenna B head and collum C penes D mid-leg and claw E leg 3, caudal view F leg 1, frontal view G ♀ paratype, vulvae H anterior gonopods, caudal view I, J posterior gonopod, caudal and frontal views, respectively. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A, B, D, E), 0.2 mm (C, F-J)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1108.85156.figure15" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/705265" pageId="0" pageNumber="89">15D</figureCitation>
). ♂ legs 1 very strongly reduced, represented by a sternum showing a pair of small, fused, paramedian, subunciform prongs directed forward, with about ten long setae at base; flanked by strongly separated, rudimentary, 2-segmented leg vestiges, second segment very large, stout, rod-shaped (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 15" captionStartId="F15" captionText="Figure 15. Glyphiulus portaliformis Zhao &amp; Liu, sp. nov., ♂ paratype A gnathochilarium and left antenna B head and collum C penes D mid-leg and claw E leg 3, caudal view F leg 1, frontal view G ♀ paratype, vulvae H anterior gonopods, caudal view I, J posterior gonopod, caudal and frontal views, respectively. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A, B, D, E), 0.2 mm (C, F-J)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1108.85156.figure15" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/705265" pageId="0" pageNumber="89">15F</figureCitation>
). ♂ legs 2 slightly hypertrophied, coxae large; penes small, much shorter than coxae, oblong-subtrapeziform, each with two or three strong setae distolaterally (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 15" captionStartId="F15" captionText="Figure 15. Glyphiulus portaliformis Zhao &amp; Liu, sp. nov., ♂ paratype A gnathochilarium and left antenna B head and collum C penes D mid-leg and claw E leg 3, caudal view F leg 1, frontal view G ♀ paratype, vulvae H anterior gonopods, caudal view I, J posterior gonopod, caudal and frontal views, respectively. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A, B, D, E), 0.2 mm (C, F-J)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1108.85156.figure15" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/705265" pageId="0" pageNumber="89">15C</figureCitation>
). ♂ legs 3 modified through coxae being especially slender and elongate (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 15" captionStartId="F15" captionText="Figure 15. Glyphiulus portaliformis Zhao &amp; Liu, sp. nov., ♂ paratype A gnathochilarium and left antenna B head and collum C penes D mid-leg and claw E leg 3, caudal view F leg 1, frontal view G ♀ paratype, vulvae H anterior gonopods, caudal view I, J posterior gonopod, caudal and frontal views, respectively. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A, B, D, E), 0.2 mm (C, F-J)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1108.85156.figure15" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/705265" pageId="0" pageNumber="89">15E</figureCitation>
). Both ♂ femora 6 and 7 normal, without modifications.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="89">
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="89">Anterior gonopods</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 15" captionStartId="F15" captionText="Figure 15. Glyphiulus portaliformis Zhao &amp; Liu, sp. nov., ♂ paratype A gnathochilarium and left antenna B head and collum C penes D mid-leg and claw E leg 3, caudal view F leg 1, frontal view G ♀ paratype, vulvae H anterior gonopods, caudal view I, J posterior gonopod, caudal and frontal views, respectively. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A, B, D, E), 0.2 mm (C, F-J)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1108.85156.figure15" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/705265" pageId="0" pageNumber="89">15H</figureCitation>
) very tall, with a portal-shaped coxosternum with about 16-18 microsetae near distal margin; apicomesal process of coxite subtriangular, tip small, slightly curved inwards. Telopodite very large and clavate, 1-segmented, lateral in position, slightly higher than lateral corner of coxite, with a field of nine microspinules at base and six strong setae apically.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="89">
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="89">Posterior gonopods</emphasis>
(Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 15" captionStartId="F15" captionText="Figure 15. Glyphiulus portaliformis Zhao &amp; Liu, sp. nov., ♂ paratype A gnathochilarium and left antenna B head and collum C penes D mid-leg and claw E leg 3, caudal view F leg 1, frontal view G ♀ paratype, vulvae H anterior gonopods, caudal view I, J posterior gonopod, caudal and frontal views, respectively. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A, B, D, E), 0.2 mm (C, F-J)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1108.85156.figure15" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/705265" pageId="0" pageNumber="89">15I, J</figureCitation>
) compact. Coxite nearly parallelogram-shaped, with an elongated field of about 14 basolateral microspinules in frontal view and with a field of 16 median microspinules in caudal view; apical and mesal parts of coxite with dense, strong and curved setae. Lamelliform lobe membranous, with a relatively long, broad, distally foliate flagellum.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="89">
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="89">Vulvae</emphasis>
very simple, bare, faintly emarginate medially (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 15" captionStartId="F15" captionText="Figure 15. Glyphiulus portaliformis Zhao &amp; Liu, sp. nov., ♂ paratype A gnathochilarium and left antenna B head and collum C penes D mid-leg and claw E leg 3, caudal view F leg 1, frontal view G ♀ paratype, vulvae H anterior gonopods, caudal view I, J posterior gonopod, caudal and frontal views, respectively. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A, B, D, E), 0.2 mm (C, F-J)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1108.85156.figure15" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/705265" pageId="0" pageNumber="89">15G</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="89" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="89">Remark.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="89">In the absence of direct troglomorphic traits, this species can only be considered as troglophilic at most.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
